# Task 5: Fault Tolerance via Global Snapshots (Chandy-Lamport)

## Background & Requirements

From the spec (FINAL-PROJECT.md):

> The application will periodically capture a **consistent global snapshot** of its state and save it on the distributed file system. On worker failure(s), the application will recover from the latest snapshot instead of starting over.

Key points:
- Uses the **Chandy-Lamport snapshot algorithm**
- Snapshots are stored in the **distributed file system** (the one from Tasks 1-3)
- Single worker failure → only that worker recovers
- Majority failure → all workers recover from the snapshot
- No existing libraries allowed (except for primality testing)

