## Recovery Logic

### Single Worker Failure
1. Coordinator detects worker timeout
2. Coordinator reads latest snapshot from DFS
3. Coordinator extracts the failed worker's state from the snapshot
4. Coordinator reassigns the failed worker's remaining work (from its last snapshotted progress offset) to a new/recovered worker
5. Replay any captured channel messages

### Majority Failure
1. All surviving processes read the latest snapshot from DFS
2. Each process restores its own state from the snapshot
3. Coordinator re-establishes the worker pool and reassigns work based on snapshot state

